ntListener` anywhere in the file. The inline per-row confirm can only be dismissed via the explicit cancel button. The intended UX — clicking anywhere outside closes it — is silently absent. This is a functional regression on a feature that was described as implemented.\n\n**MINOR — Sync I/O inside a `filter()` hot path**\n`dashboard-stubs.ts:computeMemoryStats` — `readFileSync(auditJsonPath)` is called inside `completedCycles.filter(...)`. For a project with 50+ cycles this executes synchronous disk reads per flywheel poll request. The function is already I/O-heavy, but moving the audit.json reads to a map before the filter would remove the O(N) sync reads from the critical path.\n\n**MINOR — Duplicate staleness constant across package boundary**\n`branches/+page.svelte:7` — `STALE_THRESHOLD_MS = 3 * 24 * 60 * 60 * 1000` must stay in sync with the server-side `STALE_DAYS` constant in `dashboard-stubs.ts`. The comment flags it, but a runtime mismatch would cause the UI staleness indicator and server staleness label to disagree silently.\n\n**MINOR — `MemoryEntry.metadata` typed as `unknown`, inconsistent with `CycleMemoryEntry`**\n`execute-phase.ts:56` uses `metadata?: unknown` while `memory/types.ts:CycleMemoryEntry` uses the more precise `metadata?: ReviewFindingMetadata | Record<string, unknown>`. These represent the same field on functionally identical shapes. Aligning them would close the gap and let TypeScript flag mis-shaped writes.\n\n---\n\n### Security\n\nNo concerns. The `highlightJSON` function correctly escapes `&`, `<`, `>` before regex-based span injection, so `{@html}` cannot be abused by memory entry values. Span class names are hardcoded strings with no user-controlled interpolation.\n\n---\n\n### Test Coverage\n\nStrong. Three new test files target the exact new behaviors: `audit-phase-memory.test.ts`, `cycles-approval.test.ts`, and `search.test.ts`. The flywheel test additions cover all three `memoriesInjected` cases. The `parseReviewFindingMetadata` function is exported and exercised in `phase-handlers-verification.test.ts`. The in-progress cycle search fallback is covered. No significant gaps observed.\n\n---\n\n### Verdict\n\n```\nVERDICT: REQUEST_CHANGES\nSUMMARY: Solid, well-tested sprint — one functional bug (dead cancelConfirm) and\n         two minor quality issues to resolve before merge.\nISSUES:\n  - [MAJOR]  cancelConfirm defined but never bound — \"click outside to dismiss\"\n             is silently broken. packages/dashboard/src/routes/branches/+page.svelte:210\n             Fix: add <svelte:window onclick={cancelConfirm} /> after the <svelte:head> block.\n  - [MINOR]  Sync readFileSync per cycle inside computeMemoryStats filter loop.\n             packages/server/src/routes/v5/dashboard-stubs.ts — pre-read audit files before filter.\n  - [MINOR]  STALE_THRESHOLD_MS duplicated on client; tie to a shared constant or\n             derive from the API response to prevent silent drift.\n  - [MINOR]  MemoryEntry.metadata: unknown vs CycleMemoryEntry.metadata: ReviewFindingMetadata | ...\n             — align the two interface definitions in execute-phase.ts and memory/types.ts.\nSUGGESTIONS:\n  - FILE_PATH_RE in review-phase.ts only matches ~8 root directory prefixes;\n    consider a broader heuristic (any path containing '/') for future-proofing.\n  - The tsconfig.json now depends on .svelte-kit/tsconfig.json being generated.\n    Confirm CI runs `svelte-kit sync` before tsc to avoid phantom build failures.\n```\n\n**Score: 3 / 5** — The `cancelConfirm` dead code makes a user-visible feature claim false, which is the kind of thing that fails a demo. Fix the window binding (one line), clean up the minor type inconsistency, and this is a clean 5/5 ship.""],"majorFindings":[""response": "`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`\nA few patterns stand out in this sprint worth noting:\n- The `memoriesInjected` → flywheel hit-rate pipeline is a great example of instrumenting the *write-path* to