`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The verification protocol here is the key guard against stale-review false positives. Code reviewers sometimes analyze an intermediate execute-phase snapshot — by the time the gate runs, a flagged bug may already be patched. Reading the actual file (not the review's description of it) is how the gate stays grounded in the current working tree, not in a moment that may have passed.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

